03:34.114 --> 03:36.242
Look, I ain't going
to see no doctor.

03:36.383 --> 03:38.511
If I need a doctor,
I go to a doctor.

03:38.652 --> 03:40.780
What I need is some tender
loving care, you know?

03:40.921 --> 03:44.186
And, uh, Helen here is just
the one to give it to me.

03:44.324 --> 03:45.849
Fonz...

03:45.992 --> 03:49.451
Rich, get me to a doctor
right now.

03:51.131 --> 03:53.998
<i>HOWARD: Marion, would you please
sit down and relax?</i>

03:54.134 --> 03:55.499
I'm so worried about Arthur.

03:55.635 --> 03:58.104
I mean, the boys should've been
back from the doctor by now.

03:58.238 --> 03:59.603
Well, he's gonna be just fine.

03:59.740 --> 04:02.004
Richie said he just got a bump
on the head.

04:03.610 --> 04:05.100
- Oh, Fonzie, you okay?
- Oh, oh.

04:05.245 --> 04:08.237
- How is your bump?
- Well, what did the doctor say?

04:08.381 --> 04:11.112
Hey, the doctor said
it was nothing, you know?

04:11.251 --> 04:14.744
My orbs are having a little
trouble making out shapes.

04:14.888 --> 04:20.553
Uh... there's nothing wrong
with your shape, Mrs. C.

04:20.694 --> 04:22.560
Fonzie, that's my Dad.
(chuckles)

04:22.696 --> 04:25.165
Hey, I knew that. I knew that.

04:25.298 --> 04:28.700
Nothing wrong
with your shape either, huh?

04:30.704 --> 04:33.105
Tell me, do those glasses work?

04:33.240 --> 04:34.366
Oh, yeah, this is my idea.

04:34.508 --> 04:37.136
I figured I'd give my eyes
a rest, you know?

04:37.277 --> 04:40.872
I mean, what I need now
is I need to be very comfy.

04:41.014 --> 04:43.676
That's it, just nice and comfy.

04:43.817 --> 04:45.342
(others gasp)

04:49.289 --> 04:50.654
That was... that was good, Fonz.

04:50.791 --> 04:51.952
MARION:
Well, dinner's ready.

04:52.092 --> 04:53.082
- I'll go carve the lamb.
- All right.

04:53.226 --> 04:54.625
I'll bring you a tray, Arthur.

04:54.761 --> 04:57.753
Oh, no, Mrs. C.,
I'm eating with the family.

04:57.898 --> 05:00.697
I can make it.
I know my way around.

05:00.834 --> 05:03.496
- Oh, sure, Fonz. Yeah, you got
it. -Oh, sure, Fonz. Sure. Yeah.

05:03.637 --> 05:05.571
- HOWARD: Uh, Fonzie... -Fonz.
- Uh, uh, uh, Fonz. -Uh, Fonz.

05:05.705 --> 05:07.571
Got you, got you, got you.

05:07.707 --> 05:09.698
I'm right here.

05:13.113 --> 05:16.674
The vegetables look outstanding.

05:16.817 --> 05:18.376
I'm ready.

05:18.518 --> 05:19.747
Okay.

05:19.886 --> 05:21.854
Now, I thought
we would start the meal

05:21.988 --> 05:24.582
with a nice healthful glass
of carrot juice.

05:24.724 --> 05:27.250
Oh. Carrot juice?

05:27.394 --> 05:28.520
Richard.

05:28.662 --> 05:31.256
Right, carrot juice.
Good for the eyesight.

05:31.398 --> 05:36.302
This is to my favorite
middle class American family.

05:37.671 --> 05:39.799
Hey, this is great stuff,
Mrs. C.

05:39.940 --> 05:42.375
I can see...
I can see better already.

05:42.509 --> 05:45.274
- The gravy! Well, that's...
- JOANIE: Oh.

05:45.412 --> 05:47.073
- MARION: That was a really nice
toast... -FONZIE: Thank you.

05:47.214 --> 05:48.409
-...Arthur.
- Hmm. -Yeah.

05:48.548 --> 05:50.209
Hey, listen, uh,
if nobody minds,

05:50.350 --> 05:52.375
I'm gonna help myself
to some veggies, all right?

05:52.519 --> 05:54.248
Oh, why don't you just let me
get them for you, Fonz?

05:54.387 --> 05:57.687
- I want to get 'em myself, Rich.
-|... Well, I could reach 'em...

05:58.725 --> 06:00.557
There we go.

06:00.694 --> 06:03.322
Hey, how am I doing?

06:03.463 --> 06:04.658
<i>Great.
Great.</i>

