and a little bit to the right.

13:04.217 --> 13:06.015
What were you saying, Dad?

13:07.387 --> 13:09.549
What do you want salted, Fonzie?

13:09.689 --> 13:12.215
Well, two shakes on the spuds,

13:12.358 --> 13:14.759
one on the succotash.

13:14.894 --> 13:16.623
Oh, never mind,
everything tastes the same

13:16.763 --> 13:18.162
when you're blind, anyway.

13:18.298 --> 13:21.393
Aw, come on, Fonz.
Now, you know that's not true.

13:21.534 --> 13:23.935
So just go ahead, please,
try and eat something, okay?

13:24.070 --> 13:27.335
Well, I guess you're right.

13:27.473 --> 13:29.168
Someone help me with my fork.

13:29.309 --> 13:31.710
- Of course.
- No, Mom, no.

13:31.844 --> 13:34.313
Doctor said Fonzie's got
to start doing some things

13:34.447 --> 13:35.676
for himself now.

13:35.815 --> 13:37.340
Yeah, that's great.

13:37.483 --> 13:40.180
The doctor says he's
treating me, I'm still blind.

13:40.320 --> 13:43.017
Well, he's trying, Fonz.
Why don't you?

13:43.156 --> 13:45.284
Look, your fork--
it's right here.

13:45.425 --> 13:46.688
Everything's in
its normal place.

13:46.826 --> 13:48.316
And the food--
we talked about that, right?

13:48.461 --> 13:50.190
I mean, the vegetables
up here at ten o'clock,

13:50.330 --> 13:51.820
the meat's at two o'clock
and the potatoes

13:51.964 --> 13:53.398
are right down here
at six o'clock.

13:53.533 --> 13:55.194
Now, it's all arranged
for you, Fonz.

13:55.335 --> 13:57.099
Ten o'clock, two o'clock,
six o'clock.

13:57.236 --> 13:58.635
It's easy for you; you can see.

13:58.771 --> 14:01.206
This is ridiculous, Fonzie!

14:01.341 --> 14:02.831
I mean, you used to say

14:02.975 --> 14:04.841
you could put an entire
engine together blindfolded.

14:04.977 --> 14:06.741
- That's true.
- Now you can't find your fork?

14:06.879 --> 14:10.144
Richard, now, let's not
upset Arthur's dinner.

14:10.283 --> 14:11.375
Yeah, Richie.

14:11.517 --> 14:13.679
Fonzie, last week
you were trying.

14:13.820 --> 14:15.151
I mean, you-you
couldn't see then,

14:15.288 --> 14:16.346
but you were independent.

14:16.489 --> 14:18.253
It's different;
now it's permanent.

14:18.391 --> 14:21.019
We don't know that
for certain, Fonzie.

14:21.160 --> 14:23.356
Dad, there's a very good chance
he may never see again.

14:23.496 --> 14:25.157
Cut it out, Richie.

14:25.298 --> 14:26.561
Please, Richard.

14:26.699 --> 14:29.327
Arthur needs time to learn
how to do things for himself.

14:29.469 --> 14:31.062
So when's he gonna start, Mom?

14:31.204 --> 14:33.866
He'll start when
he makes the adjustment.

14:34.006 --> 14:35.701
Right now, he needs our help.

14:35.842 --> 14:37.571
Help is fine.

14:37.710 --> 14:39.178
But he's just
got to try himself!

14:39.312 --> 14:40.541
And you can do it, Fonz.

14:40.680 --> 14:42.774
Look, there's a saying:

14:42.915 --> 14:45.179
"When the going gets tough,
the tough get going."

14:45.318 --> 14:47.343
Well, that's just
a very cute expression

14:47.487 --> 14:49.581
when you're playing
silly intramural games.

14:49.722 --> 14:51.656
This is life.
And this conversation is over.

14:51.791 --> 14:53.589
Finis. The end. You understand?

14:53.726 --> 14:55.592
Joanie, would you
help me upstairs, please?

14:55.728 --> 14:57.787
- I'm a little too upset to eat.
- Help me!

14:57.930 --> 14:59.523
Salt me, pick up my fork.

14:59.665 --> 15:01.827
Fonzie, I never thought
I would ever say this to you...

15:01.968 --> 15:03.265
but you're a coward.

15:03.403 --> 15:04.495
You call me a coward?

15:04.637 --> 15:06.105
Yeah, you want me
to help myself?

15:06.239 --> 15:07.604
- Yes! -All right,
I'll help myself. There!

15:07.740 --> 15:09.708
That's what happens when
I help myself! You see that?!

15:09.842 --> 15:11.936
I'm useless! I'm blind!

15:12.078 --> 15:15.013
You may be blind, Fonz,
but let me tell you something.

15:15.148 --> 15:17.742
It's your decision
to be useless.

15:31.397 --> 15:33.957
<i>JQANE:
Okay, Fonz, in the first panel,</i>

15:34.100 --> 15:36.728
Dagwood is stretched out
on the couch sleeping.

15:36.869 --> 15:39.031
Is he dreaming about
sawing a log in half

15:39.172 --> 15:41.334
or are there just a bunch
of "Zs" over his head?

15:41.474 --> 15:43.966
Oh, just "Zs."
I-It's the Katzenjammer Kids

15:44.110 --> 15:45.942
-who saw the logs.
- Yeah. Right, right, right.

15:46.078 --> 15:47.910
- Okay, the next panel...
- Fonzie?

15:48.047 --> 15:48.912
- Yeah?
- It's me.

15:49.048 --> 15:50.072
So what?

15:50.216 --> 15:51.650
Keep going.
What else happens there?

15:51.784 --> 15:53.809
- Okay. He gets up...
- Joanie, uh,

15:53.953 --> 15:55.443
I'd like to be alone
with Fonzie, please,

15:55.588 --> 15:56.714
if you don't mind.

15:58.524 --> 15:59.753
Is it okay, Fonzie?

15:59.892 --> 16:01.053
Yeah.

16:01.194 --> 16:03.162
All right.
I'll be right downstairs,

16:03.296 --> 16:05.663
and when you're ready
to do the crossword puzzle,

16:05.798 --> 16:07.596
I'll be there, okay?

16:07.733 --> 16:09.861
Yeah.

16:10.002 --> 16:11.993
You be nice.

16:16.175 --> 16:20.373
Well, Fonz, I just, uh,
brought you a present.

16:20.513 --> 16:23.210
Yeah? You're trying to make up,
I ain't buying it.

16:23.349 --> 16:25.215
Well, wait till you find out
what it is, Fonz.

16:25.351 --> 16:26.477
I think you're gonna like it.

16:26.619 --> 16:28.553
We went to a lot of trouble
to get it for you.

16:28.688 --> 16:29.553
What do you mean "we"?

16:29.689 --> 16:31.748
Who else is in my room here?

16:32.792 --> 16:35.727
It's...

16:35.862 --> 16:37.762
It's nobody, right, Biff?

16:37.897 --> 16:39.422
(deep voice):
Right, Duke.

16:39.565 --> 16:41.533
Come on.

16:41.667 --> 16:43.294
Is that Ralph and Potsie?

16:44.337 --> 16:45.361
Fonz, please don't hit us.

16:45.505 --> 16:46.529
We didn't mean to do it.

16:46.672 --> 16:48.140
I'm telling you,
Richie made me do it.

16:48.274 --> 16:49.469
- We're pawns.
- Pawns?

16:49.609 --> 16:51.737
We're dead men!
Let's get out of here, Malph!

16:51.878 --> 16:54.404
No names, Potsie!

16:54.547 --> 16:57.039
What's going on here, Rich?
What's happening here?

16:57.183 --> 17:01.017
Well, we thought, uh, you'd like
to have your motorcycle

17:01.153 --> 17:03.588
-up here with you.
- Heyyy.

17:08.661 --> 17:11.323
My bike doesn't go
clackety-clack.

17:11.464 --> 17:14.398
Yeah, well, it, uh...
it does now.

17:14.534 --> 17:16.127
See you around.

17:20.373 --> 17:23.240
I hate your guts, Cunningham!
You hear me?!

17:23.376 --> 17:26.402
- I hate your guts!
-(metal clanking)

17:26.546 --> 17:29.538
How could they do this to you?

17:31.551 --> 17:34.350
How could you
do this to me, huh?

17:34.487 --> 17:36.751
I thought
I was your favorite person.

17:36.889 --> 17:38.880
(exhaling sharply)

17:49.001 --> 17:50.992
My bike.

17:54.006 --> 17:56.202
Carburetor.

17:56.342 --> 17:59.573
Hello, little carburetor.

17:59.712 --> 18:01.043
Wait a minute.

18:01.180 --> 18:03.148
(metal clanking)

18:03.282 --> 18:05.580
Yeah.

18:05.718 --> 18:07.379
You two parts shouldn't be...

18:07.520 --> 18:09.386
There you go.
You should be together, huh?

18:09.522 --> 18:10.990
Doesn't that feel better?

18:11.123 --> 18:12.613
Yeah.

18:12.758 --> 18:14.624
All right, look, don't go away.

18:14.760 --> 18:16.592
I'm just gonna get my toolbox.

18:16.729 --> 18:18.720
I'll be right back.

18:32.044 --> 18:34.775
Is that you?

18:34.914 --> 18:36.905
It's me.

18:38.618 --> 18:40.313
Well?

18:40.453 --> 18:42.979
Well, it's, uh...

18:43.122 --> 18:44.681
it's terrific.

18:44.824 --> 18:46.690
Yeah.

18:46.826 --> 18:49.761
It's a great expression,
you know?

18:49.895 --> 18:52.956
When the, uh, going gets tough,
the tough get going.

18:53.099 --> 18:55.466
Yeah, it is. You know, I...

18:55.601 --> 18:57.865
wish I'd said it.
(chuckles)

18:58.004 --> 18:59.301
You did.

19:00.573 --> 19:01.631
Thanks.

19:02.942 --> 19:04.535
I've been doing
a lot of thinking, you know?

19:04.677 --> 19:06.338
Maybe I'm wasting
a lot of time here.

19:06.479 --> 19:08.948
I mean, I got a whole life
ahead of me, you know?

19:09.081 --> 19:11.880
I got hands to work,
lips to play.

19:13.619 --> 19:15.485
I-I'd like my jacket.

19:15.621 --> 19:19.080
- Would you get me my jacket,
please? -Got it. You got it.

19:19.225 --> 19:20.886
All right.

19:21.027 --> 19:22.552
This is the Fonz talking now.

19:22.695 --> 19:24.686
- Here's your jacket.
- Thanks.

19:30.302 --> 19:32.327
I feel better already.

19:32.471 --> 19:33.461
- Yeah, well, you look great.
- Yeah.

19:33.606 --> 19:35.040
I think now
I'm in business here.

19:35.174 --> 19:36.266
(both chuckle)

19:36.409 --> 19:37.706
Thanks.

19:37.843 --> 19:40.505
I'm still very scared, you know.

19:40.646 --> 19:43.240
I know. I know, Fonz.
But you're not gonna be alone.

19:43.382 --> 19:45.441
There are a lot of organizations
in Milwaukee

19:45.584 --> 19:47.052
that are gonna...
are gonna help you.

19:47.186 --> 19:50.349
Well, maybe I can get
a seeing eye chick.

19:50.489 --> 19:52.150
(chuckles)

19:52.291 --> 19:54.316
As long as she ain't a dog.

19:54.460 --> 19:55.791
Yeah, right.

19:55.928 --> 19:57.623
Well, I'm sure you're gonna have
plenty of volunteers.

19:57.763 --> 20:01.461
And... and if you need us...

20:01.600 --> 20:04.626
well, then you got a family
downstairs that...

20:04.770 --> 20:06.397
loves you very much.

20:06.539 --> 20:08.530
Hey.

20:10.876 --> 20:13.868
What do you say, you and me,
we go down to Arnold's?

20:14.013 --> 20:16.004
- That's an idea.
- Yeah? You like that idea?

20:16.148 --> 20:18.082
All right, look, uh, the door
is right over here, Fonz.

20:18.217 --> 20:19.412
I know where the door is.

20:19.552 --> 20:21.748
I've been-been finding it
for three years now.

20:21.887 --> 20:23.355
- Oh, right.
- Huh? Look at that.

20:23.489 --> 20:25.355
- I got the door, right? Huh?
-(chuckles)

20:25.491 --> 20:27.482
Door's open.

20:31.130 --> 20:33.258
You're a terrific buddy.

20:33.399 --> 20:36.528
Thanks.

20:36.669 --> 20:39.195
This is, uh...

20:39.338 --> 20:41.705
very hard for me to say.

20:41.841 --> 20:43.935
Well-well, then, listen,
you don't have to say it, Fonz.

20:44.076 --> 20:45.066
Yes, I do.

20:45.211 --> 20:48.237
No, you don't
have to say it. You...

20:48.380 --> 20:51.315
Well... go ahead.

20:53.319 --> 20:54.650
Cunningham...

20:54.787 --> 20:55.913
Yeah, Fonz.

20:56.055 --> 20:59.514
...if you ever
touch my bike again,

20:59.658 --> 21:02.150
I'm gonna disconnect
your freckles.

21:04.130 --> 21:07.327
Aw, you didn't have
to say that, Fonz.

21:07.466 --> 21:08.934
You got a deal.

21:09.068 --> 21:10.331
All right. Let's go.

21:10.469 --> 21:12.460
All right.

21:19.712 --> 21:22.511
Oh, I'm so proud of Arthur.

21:22.648 --> 21:24.514
The instructor said
he's learning so fast,

21:24.650 --> 21:26.641
he's already getting around
with his cane.

21:26.786 --> 21:28.515
(chuckles) And girls, too.

21:28.654 --> 21:31.055
He had a lot
of catching up to do.

21:31.190 --> 21:33.852
Well, he closed
Inspiration Point to the public.

21:35.494 --> 21:36.791
Oh, Richard.

21:36.929 --> 21:38.397
Arthur!

21:38.531 --> 21:41.523
- Hi, Fonz. -Hi, Fonz.
- Hey, folks.

21:43.536 --> 21:45.197
Nice to see you, Mrs. C.

21:45.337 --> 21:47.203
Well, it's nice
to see you, Arthur.

21:47.339 --> 21:49.068
Hey, Joanie, you look great.

21:49.208 --> 21:51.199
Oh, Fonz, I-l look a mess.

21:51.343 --> 21:53.675
I think pink looks
very good on you.

21:53.813 --> 21:56.373
Arthur, you can see!

21:56.515 --> 21:59.007
- Fonzie!
- Yeah. Yeah. I can see!

21:59.151 --> 22:00.812
I mean, look, I was going
to the doctor, right,

22:00.953 --> 22:02.978
for a regular treatment, and
he starts playing with my eyes,

22:03.122 --> 22:04.920
you know?
And all of a sudden, bang,

22:05.057 --> 22:07.116
I could see shapes
and colors, you know?

22:07.259 --> 22:09.318
Oh, what beautiful colors.

22:09.461 --> 22:11.589
- Now, everything is still
a little fuzzy, -RICHIE: Yeah.

22:11.730 --> 22:14.256
But he says that, uh,
if I continue to go

22:14.400 --> 22:16.596
and I go for my treatments,
in just a few days,

22:16.735 --> 22:18.464
- I should be back to normal,
you know? -HOWARD: Oh.

22:18.604 --> 22:20.094
-100%.
- JOANIE: Oh.

22:20.239 --> 22:21.400
What a relief.

22:21.540 --> 22:23.269
You want to talk about relief,
you ought to see Al.

22:23.409 --> 22:25.468
- He's still draped over
the pinball machine. -(laughter)

22:25.611 --> 22:27.807
- Oh, wait till I tell everybody.
- Oh. Oh, I have to tell Jenny.

22:27.947 --> 22:29.540
- Everybody wants to know what
happened. -(excited chatter)

22:29.682 --> 22:32.151
Wait a minute! Wait a minute!
Everybody, come back here.

22:32.284 --> 22:34.275
I want to say something.

22:35.721 --> 22:37.849
Yeah.

22:37.990 --> 22:41.756
What I want to say is that,
uh, well...

22:41.894 --> 22:42.861
I think he wants to say...

22:42.995 --> 22:46.329
I know what I want to say.

22:46.465 --> 22:48.433
First of all,
I want to say thanks.

22:50.069 --> 22:51.537
Second of all...

22:51.670 --> 22:53.536
I want to say
that I'm very happy

22:53.672 --> 22:55.663
that you're all
a part of my life.

22:56.842 --> 23:00.176
-(chuckles)
- Oh, Arthur. -Aw.

23:15.461 --> 23:16.724
FONZIE:
To the stairway.

23:16.862 --> 23:18.057
- To the stairway.
- Fonz, Fonz.

23:18.197 --> 23:20.689
- What? -We already toasted
the stairway.

23:20.833 --> 23:23.063
We've done the whole house.

23:23.202 --> 23:25.603
Let me tell you something,
you've been in darkness like me

23:25.738 --> 23:28.070
for a week,
everything looks fabuloso.

23:28.207 --> 23:31.040
- Arthur's right.
Let's keep on toasting. -Right.

23:31.176 --> 23:32.405
-(doorbell rings) -FONZIE:
To the doorbell. -JOANIE: Oh.

23:32.544 --> 23:33.477
To the doorbell.

23:33.612 --> 23:34.875
I'll get it.

23:35.014 --> 23:37.210
I got it.

23:37.349 --> 23:39.374
Hey, Rich...

23:39.518 --> 23:41.714
All right, Fonz,
don't kill them.

23:41.854 --> 23:44.050
- Uh, they meant very well.
-(doorbell rings)

23:44.189 --> 23:47.386
(sighs) I understand.
I understand, Mr. C.

23:47.526 --> 23:49.051
All right, I'll be gentle.

23:49.194 --> 23:50.787
- Don't say a word, all right?
- Well...

23:50.930 --> 23:53.922
Let them in. Let them in.

23:55.200 --> 23:56.929
- RICHIE: Let them in?
- Let them in.

23:58.203 --> 23:59.932
- Hi, guys. Come on in.
- Hey, Rich.

24:00.072 --> 24:01.665
- Hello, Warren.
- Mrs. C.

24:01.807 --> 24:04.071
- Mr. C., Joanie.
- Mrs. C.

24:04.209 --> 24:06.837
Hey, everybody. Hey, Fonz.

24:06.979 --> 24:10.415
Fonz, Fonz,
have we got a surprise for you.

24:10.549 --> 24:12.950
Hey, that's great 'cause I got
a surprise for you, too.

24:13.085 --> 24:15.577
Oh. Come on, Fonz,
ours first, all right?

24:15.721 --> 24:17.086
All right, all right, go first.

24:17.222 --> 24:20.055
All right, Fonz...
(chuckles)

24:20.192 --> 24:22.388
we took your bike apart again!

24:22.528 --> 24:24.189
More therapy.

24:24.330 --> 24:25.820
Yep.

24:25.965 --> 24:26.932
My turn?

24:27.066 --> 24:28.659
- Sure.
- Sure. (chuckles)

24:28.801 --> 24:30.860
Richie, why don't you toss me
one of those oranges

24:31.003 --> 24:32.164
on the table over there.

24:32.304 --> 24:33.465
Oh, sure, Fonz.

24:33.605 --> 24:36.074
Here you go.

24:36.208 --> 24:37.266
Thanks.

24:37.409 --> 24:39.343
Hey, Fonz,
that's really terrific.

24:39.478 --> 24:42.709
Thank you.

24:42.848 --> 24:45.340
Whoop. Whoop.

24:45.484 --> 24:46.349
Whoop.

24:46.485 --> 24:48.681
Potsie, he can see! He can see!

24:48.821 --> 24:50.755
Let's get out of here!
Let's get out of here!

24:50.889 --> 24:52.755
(deep voice):
It was all Duke's idea.

